ing, and functioning within a student-centred collaborative, multi-use space. Experience in managing a school library is an asset. This includes managing and curating the physical, electronic, and online texts and learning resources within a school library. The candidate will be part of a dynamic campus environment where highly motivated students and dedicated staff combine to create a vital, inclusive community culture. Our faculty contributes to both curricular and co-curricular programming, supporting academics and school life opportunities for students. Teachers receive competitive compensation and may apply for support for professional development. The candidate must hold a valid Manitoba Teaching Certificate or be eligible to obtain one. Qualified applicants should forward their applications, including a cover letter, résumé, a recent teaching evaluation, and the names of three references by Monday, April 25, 2024, to: Attn: Ms. Michelle Woods, B.A., HRMHuman Resources CoordinatorSt. John’s-Ravenscourt School400 South DriveWinnipeg, MB R3T 3K5 F: 204.477.2466 E: careers@sjr.mb.ca By submitting an application for employment, applicants consent to the School conducting inquiries into suitability for employment by contacting references provided and/or former employers, verification of academic records and any information publicly available online, including social media. The duration of this consent is limited from the time of my application to the time that hiring for the 2024-2025 school year is completed. This information will not be shared with any other organization or individual outside of the School, without your request or prior authorization, unless required or permitted by law. In accordance with its employment equity policy, SJR encourages applications from all qualified individuals. We thank all who apply; only those candidates selected for an interview will be contacted. SJR is committed to promoting the welfare of our students.All qualified applicants will be required to provide a clear Criminal Record Check and Child Abuse Registry Check prior to commencement of employment. Compensation $67,995-$120,689 DOQ Closes: 25 April, 2024 St. John's-Ravenscourt School Winnipeg , MB Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
