Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Collections Manager Yorkton , SK Description The Collection Manager, under the supervision of the Regional Director, is responsible for collections management, digital library services, acquisitions, and statistics reporting for the all branches within the region. Employees in this class have a high degree of independence within their duties and have considerable autonomy. This position oversees a number of headquarters employees and works directly with branch library staff, vendors, provincial library and SILS staff, and the management team.Duties &amp; Responsibilities:Design collections development standards and goals in conjunction with Regional Director and be responsible for implementation of these standards and goals. Primary acquisition of all new materials, including direct purchasing and/or creating and monitoring Automatic Release Plans (ARP) as required. Receive, evaluate, and process donated library materials from all branches. Allocate all new and rehomed materials based on collections standards and goals. Create annual fund hierarchy and monitor purchasing progress against budget goals. Maintain vendor files and relationships for acquisition of new materials. Maintain cataloging standards for new materials, including generating new MARC records, verifying and uploading vendor cataloging, and ordering cataloging from PLLO as required. Oversee, conduct purchasing, provide support, and evaluate digital library resources for the region in line with collections standards and goals. Generate collections, circulations, acquisitions, and branch statistics and analysis. Utilize reporting and statistical analysis to evaluate acquisitions and collections success and modify procedures to ensure compliance with collections goals. Manage assigned and floating collections on the branch and regional levels. Operate and facilitate ILLO program within region. Generate resources, support, and communicate with branch libraries regarding collections, acquisitions, processing, library systems, and digital resources. Work collaboratively with Regional Director, Branch Supervisor, and Office Manager to develop and implement library policy, procedures, and guidelines. Assist in the compilation and distribution of the regional newsletter in conjunction with Regional Director and Branch Supervisor. Assist in the development and maintenance of branch manual content in conjunction with Regional Director and Branch Supervisor. Direct acquisitions and processing staff to facilitate these duties as required. Perform other duties as assigned. Qualifications:MLIS or other relevant graduate degreeAt least two years of acquisitions and purchasing experienceAt least two years of library collections experience A candidate working on their MLIS,
especially with additional experience in acquisitions and/or reporting
statistics with analysis would be considered a viable candidate.Required qualifications: Effective
Communication, customer service and organizational skills, flexibility, work
independently or part of a team, and maintain confidentiality. Criminal records check required.Apply by Email to Kathryn Foley, director@parklandlibrary.caInterviews may begin March 20, 2024 Compensation $65,000 - $75,000 dependent on education and experience Closes: 18 April, 2024 Parkland Regional Library Yorkton , SK Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
