Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? University Librarian Prince George , BC Description Located in the spectacular landscape of northern British Columbia, UNBC is a leading research-intensive university in Northern British Columbia with five faculties and the Division of Medical Sciences. Home to over 3,000 students, UNBC consistently ranked 2nd in Canada in its category in the annual Maclean’s University rankings, and 3rd for total research income. UNBC also recently placed among the top five percent of higher education institutions worldwide by the Times Higher Education World University Rankings. The University provides outstanding undergraduate and graduate learning opportunities that explore cultures, health, economies, sciences, and the environment.The UNBC Library offers state-of-the-art research technology, a learning commons, research data centre, and a full range of services to students and faculty in an attractive four-story building featuring an impressive wood and light-filled atrium, comprehensive archives, and library holdings reaching 800,000 items. The Northern BC Archives, housed in the Library, is dedicated to acquire, preserve and provide access to materials that are related to the institutional history of UNBC and the culture and History of Northern British Columbia. Reporting to the Provost and working closely with the VP Research, the Deans of the five faculties, the AVP of the Division of Medical Sciences, and others, the University Librarian is a visionary leader at the forefront of library and archival sciences who will lead the library and its dedicated professional staff as it meets the challenges of information and knowledge management in the digital age. UNBC is looking forward to welcoming a new member to the community to have a long-term and profound impact on this exceptional post-secondary institution. UNBC encourages applications from all qualified individuals, including women, Indigenous people, visible minorities, and persons with disabilities. All qualified candidates are encouraged to apply, although Canadians and Permanent Residents will be given priority. The expected salary range for this position is $175,000 to $190,000. To apply for this opportunity, please click Apply. For more information, please contact unbclibrarian@boyden.com We thank all applicants for their interest in this position. Please note that we will only be in contact with those individuals moving forward with our client. Compensation $175,000 to $190,000 Closes: 28 April, 2024 University of Northern British Columbia Prince George , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
